This paper likely belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it deals with inferring social structure and dominance relationships in a group of monkeys. It also involves the use of RFID tracking data, which could fall under the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of quantitative criteria and the construction of graphs, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of histograms and dot products, which could fall under the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
